A prolonged wait is the norm for this corner store. Tucked within a gas station on the corner of a busy intersection, there is usually a line.  When there is no line, both windows for ordering or pick up are unoccupied and there is still a wait.  The donut selection is sparse; however, the staff are helpful and engaging when they complete an order. --- Update: the store's narrative has evolved into no donuts except 'ghost pepper'.
